{% extends "base_pullback_ratio_rules.j2" %}

{% block analysis_guidelines %}
Run the level-focused pullback-ratio strategy.

Use support/resistance as the main signal source:
- BUY only after confirmed support reaction, failed breakdown reclaim, or breakout-retest hold.
- SELL only after confirmed resistance reaction, failed breakout failure, or breakdown-retest fail.
- Treat levels as candidates, not signals. The level must produce visible candle confirmation.
- If the current price is in the middle between visible levels, HOLD.
- If the next opposing level is too close after a {{ "%.0f"|format((pullback_ratio|float) * 100) }}% pullback-limit fill, HOLD.
{% endblock %}


